.TH WS-RUN-AUDIO 1 "January 2026" "ws-node 1.4.1" "WildlifeSystems Commands"
.SH NAME
ws-run-audio \- run audio recording for WildlifeSystems
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ws-run-audio
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ws-run-audio
manages audio recording sessions for WildlifeSystems nodes. It reads
configuration from
.I /etc/ws/audio.conf
and controls the recording hardware and software.
.PP
This command is typically run by a systemd service (ws-audio.service) rather than
invoked directly.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/ws/audio.conf
JSON configuration file for audio recording.
.TP
.I /var/log/ws-run-audio.log
Standard output log file.
.TP
.I /var/log/ws-run-audio-error.log
Error log file.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ws-upload (1),
